  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Issue_management_arm.Disposition">
        A <b>Disposition</b> is a type of  

        <express_ref linkend="approval:arm:Approval_arm.Approval"/> which records the decision of how to resolve an Issue and provides links to the <express_ref linkend="activity_as_realized:arm:Activity_as_realized_arm.Activity_actual"/> that made the decision

<note number="1">A <b>Disposition</b> will normally reference both the <express_ref linkend="work_order:arm:Work_order_arm.Work_order"/> or <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request"/> in the role of "subject", and the <express_ref linkend="activity_as_realized:arm:Activity_as_realized_arm.Activity_actual"/> at which the disposition was made, here in the role of "disposing action".</note>
<note number="2">Where a meeting decides the disposition of several issues, an <express_ref linkend="activity_as_realized:arm:Activity_as_realized_arm.Activity_actual"/> would provide the record of each individual disposition, and a collector <express_ref linkend="activity_as_realized:arm:Activity_as_realized_arm.Activity_actual"/> would define the overall meeting parameters, such as the date and the attendance list.</note>

	</ext_description>
